  "root_text": {
    "iti21:0.1": "Itivuttaka 21 ",
    "iti21:0.2": "Ekakanipāta ",
    "iti21:0.3": "Tatiyavagga ",
    "iti21:0.4": "Pasannacittasutta ",
    "iti21:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti21:2.1": "“Idhāhaṁ, bhikkhave, ekaccaṁ puggalaṁ pasannacittaṁ evaṁ cetasā ceto paricca pajānāmi: ",
    "iti21:2.2": "‘imamhi cāyaṁ samaye puggalo kālaṁ kareyya yathābhataṁ nikkhitto evaṁ sagge’. ",
    "iti21:2.3": "Taṁ kissa hetu? ",
    "iti21:2.4": "Cittaṁ hissa, bhikkhave, pasannaṁ. ",
    "iti21:2.5": "Cetopasādahetu kho pana, bhikkhave, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā sugatiṁ saggaṁ lokaṁ upapajjantī”ti. ",
    "iti21:2.6": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti21:2.7": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti21:3.1": "“Pasannacittaṁ ñatvāna, ",
    "iti21:3.2": "ekaccaṁ idha puggalaṁ; ",
    "iti21:3.3": "Etamatthañca byākāsi, ",
    "iti21:3.4": "buddho bhikkhūna santike. ",
    "iti21:4.1": "Imamhi cāyaṁ samaye, ",
    "iti21:4.2": "kālaṁ kayirātha puggalo; ",
    "iti21:4.3": "Sugatiṁ upapajjeyya, ",
    "iti21:4.4": "cittaṁ hissa pasāditaṁ. ",
    "iti21:5.1": "Yathā haritvā nikkhipeyya, ",
    "iti21:5.2": "evamevaṁ tathāvidho; ",
    "iti21:5.3": "Cetopasādahetu hi, ",
    "iti21:5.4": "sattā gacchanti suggatin”ti. ",
    "iti21:6.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti21:6.2": "Paṭhamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti21:0.1": "So It Was Said 21 ",
    "iti21:0.2": "The Book of the Ones ",
    "iti21:0.3": "Chapter Three ",
    "iti21:0.4": "A Pure Mind ",
    "iti21:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti21:2.1": "“Mendicants, when I’ve comprehended the mind of an individual whose mind is pure, I understand: ",
    "iti21:2.2": "‘If this individual were to die right now, they would be placed in heaven as if delivered there.’ ",
    "iti21:2.3": "Why is that? ",
    "iti21:2.4": "Because their mind is pure. ",
    "iti21:2.5": "Purity of mind is the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm.” ",
    "iti21:2.6": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti21:2.7": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti21:3.1": "“Knowing an individual’s ",
    "iti21:3.2": "pure mind, ",
    "iti21:3.3": "the Buddha explained this matter ",
    "iti21:3.4": "in the mendicants’ presence. ",
    "iti21:4.1": "If that individual ",
    "iti21:4.2": "were to die at this time, ",
    "iti21:4.3": "they’d be reborn in heaven, ",
    "iti21:4.4": "for their mind is pure. ",
    "iti21:5.1": "That sort is raised up as surely ",
    "iti21:5.2": "as if they’d been carried and put there. ",
    "iti21:5.3": "For purity of mind is the reason ",
    "iti21:5.4": "sentient beings go to a good place.” ",
    "iti21:6.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
